Interface ClientExecutableMessage

All Known Implementing Classes:
BuildPhaseMessage, BuildProposalMessage, DomeBuildMessage, FirstPlayerProposalMessage, GameEndMessage, GameStartMessage, GodChoiceProposalMessage, GodSublistProposalMessage, GodUpdateMessage, LobbySizeMessage, MovePhaseMessage, MoveProposalMessage, NotificationMessage, PhaseMessage, PlayerRegisterMessage, ProposalMessage, TowerIncrementMessage, UnregisterPlayerMessage, UsernameMessage, WorkerAddMessage, WorkerChoicePhaseMessage, WorkerIndexMessage, WorkerInitialPositionMessage, WorkerMoveMessage, WorkerPlacementPhaseMessage, YesNoMessage
public interface ClientExecutableMessage
extends Message
A message send from the server that contains executable instructions. This corresponds more-or-less to a client-side implementation of a server action, except that the client is "dumb" and has to simply display what the server says.
